From 9ddc01467992ab688f0b17cc3a6949618f370b54 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 21:29:58 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add lookahead peak limiter on the output (milestone 6)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Replaces the bare clamp(-1,1) with a proper brickwall limiter:
- 256-sample ring-buffer lookahead (~5.8 ms) — stack allocated, no heap.
- Instant attack: gain reduction applied before the peak arrives at the output.
- One-pole release filter — configurable 10–500 ms (default 100 ms).
- Threshold/ceiling param -12 to 0 dBFS (default -0.3 dBFS).
- New OUTPUT section in the UI with Ceiling and Release sliders.

Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
